text: Crassispira degrangei is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pseudomelatomidae, the turrids and allies.MNHN, Paris: Crassispira degrangei Fossils have been found in Oligocene strata of Aquitaine, France. ==References== * Lozouet (P.), 2017 Les Conoidea de l’Oligocène supérieur (Chattien) du bassin de l’Adour (Sud-Ouest de la France). Cossmanniana, t. 19, p. 1-179 degrangei Category:Gastropods described in 1931
title: Crassispira degrangei
